About this hotel

Adjacent to the Jemaa el-Fnaa market square, this chic hotel is an 8-minute walk from the Parc Lalla Hasna, 4 km from the Majorelle Garden and 4 km from the Marrakesh Menara Airport.

Check-in time: 3:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    Chris Mawson4 years ago on Google
    5/5
    We ate at the Riad’s terrace restaurant. It’s a lovely local place tucked away up 3 flights of stairs on the rooftop. The views are pretty typical of Marrakech as it doesn’t look over the square itself but is nice enough. It seems popular …
    We ate at the Riad’s terrace restaurant. It’s a lovely local place tucked away up 3 flights of stairs on the rooftop. The views are pretty typical of Marrakech as it doesn’t look over the square itself but is nice enough. It seems popular with locals and walking tour guides who drop off their groups looking for lunch or dinner.
    There is an a la carte and set menu, we opted for the lunch set menu which costs 180MAD each. This contains a selection of fresh salads, bread and olives as a starter. Then a main, then tea and fruit for dessert.
    The food was all fresh tasting and looked great. We thoroughly enjoyed it and left feeling satisfied and would definitely go back. Service was quick and polite.
    Would recommend.

    Very typical Moroccan accommodation, expect rather basic but comfortable stay. The riad has a few floors (2-3) in a 4 wall fashion and an open courtyard in the middle. The rooms were small but clean, the beds comfortable. Windows open on the courtyard and you could hear people talking in the hall as clearly as if they were in the room. Personally I liked it but those who prefer more intimacy might take this into consideration. I don't recall there was heating in the room so plan your stay around the weather (though the duvets were really warm). Wifi was included but fairly weak. Dining area is on the top floor + terrace which overlooks the mosque and the Jemaa el-Fna. No fuss, would go back.

    - colazione a buffet dal sapore tradizionale
    NEGATIVO
    - colazione: poca varietà
    - stanza: la nostra era a piano terra, davvero piccola per un letto matrimoniale, ma il bagno era grandissimo
    - poche prese della corrente: per i tecnologici consiglio una ciabatta multipresa
    - reception: mai un sorriso
    CONSIGLIO
    - stanze a piano terra: bellissimo godere della pace del bel cortile
    NON CONSIGLIO
    - non adatto a persone con difficoltà motorie: non c'è ascensore

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakesh’s original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.

    About this hotel

    Adjacent to the Jemaa el-Fnaa market square, this chic hotel is an 8-minute walk from the Parc Lalla Hasna, 4 km from the Majorelle Garden and 4 km from the Marrakesh Menara Airport. …

    Down-to-earth rooms include TVs, safes and private bathrooms. Suites add living rooms with fireplaces.

    Amenities include a stylish courtyard with seating, plus a refined restaurant with terrace seating.
